text: Helene "Lena" Asmus (; May 5, 1982, Omsk, Russia) is a Russian and German rhythmic gymnast. Asmus competed for Germany in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney. There she was 17th in the qualification and didn't advance to the final of 10 competitors. == References == == External links == * Lena Asmus at Sports- Reference.com Category:1982 births Category:Living people Category:Russian rhythmic gymnasts Category:German rhythmic gymnasts Category:Gymnasts at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Germany Category:Sportspeople from Omsk
